<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
  <head>
    <%- include('./partials/head'); %>
    <title>Privacy Policy - Climb Timer</title>
    <style>
      body {
        font-family: system-ui, sans-serif;
        line-height: 1.6;
        max-width: 800px;
        margin: 2rem auto;
        padding: 0 1rem;
        color: #222;
      }
      h1,
      h2 {
        color: #111;
      }
      h1 {
        font-size: 2em;
        margin-bottom: 0.5em;
      }
      h2 {
        margin-top: 2em;
        font-size: 1.4em;
      }
      p {
        margin: 1em 0;
      }
      ul {
        margin: 0.5em 0 1.5em 1.5em;
      }
    </style>
  </head>
  <body>
    <header><%- include('./partials/header', {navItem: 'login'}); %></header>
    <main>
      <div class="content-container">
        <h1>Privacy Policy</h1>
        <p><em>Last updated: April 26th 2025</em></p>

        <p>Welcome to <strong>Climb Timer</strong>!</p>

        <p>
          We care about your privacy and want to be transparent about what data
          we collect and how we use it. This Privacy Policy explains it simply.
        </p>

        <h2>1. Information We Collect</h2>

        <ul>
          <li>
            <strong>Account Information:</strong><br />
            If you decide to <strong>sign up</strong>, we collect your email
            address and store the timers you create in connection with your
            account.<br />
            If you do not sign up, we do <strong>not</strong> collect any
            personal information.
          </li>

          <li>
            <strong>Cookies:</strong><br />
            We use cookies <strong>only</strong> to locally store timers you
            create without an account. These cookies stay on your device, and
            you control them. We do not use cookies for advertising or tracking
            across sites.
          </li>
        </ul>

        <h2>2. How We Use Your Information</h2>

        <ul>
          <li>
            If you have an account, we use your email and saved timers so you
            can view and manage them across your devices.
          </li>
          <li>
            If you do not have an account, the connection to your timers are stored in your
            browser using cookies. 
          </li>
        </ul>

        <h2>3. Data Sharing</h2>
        <p>
          We do <strong>not</strong> share your personal information with third
          parties.
        </p>

        <h2>4. Your Choices</h2>

        <ul>
          <li>
            <strong>Without an account:</strong> You can dissociate from your timers
            anytime by clearing your browser cookies.
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>With an account:</strong> You can delete your account and
            all associated data at any time through your account settings.
          </li>
        </ul>

        <h2>5. Contact Us</h2>
        <p>
          If you have any questions about this Privacy Policy, feel free to
          reach out:
        </p>
        <p>
          <strong>Email</strong>:
          <a href="mailto:climbtimer.webapp@gmail.com"
            >climbtimer.webapp@gmail.com</a
          >
        </p>
      </div>
    </main>
    <footer><%- include('./partials/footer'); %></footer>
  </body>
</html>
